+### Per-tick semantics
+
+`reckoner.schedulerConfig` is re-read from `guild.json` on every
+tick fire so operators can hot-edit. The Reckoner does not narrow
+this value — each scheduler's `validateConfig`, when declared, is
+the trust boundary. A `validateConfig` throw fail-loud-skips the
+entire tick: no rows are written for any candidate, and the writs
+stay in `new` for the next tick to re-attempt with the corrected
+config. Same for an `evaluate` throw: the entire tick is abandoned
+and no rows land for any candidate.
+
+The narrowed result becomes `SchedulerInput.config` for the
+immediately-following `evaluate` call. The `SchedulerInput`
+carries the whole surviving candidate set — schedulers see every
+held writ in one batch (the per-writ `candidates: [writ]` shape of
+the per-call CDC era is gone). Decisions are applied to candidates
+in candidate order; per-writ failures are isolated (one writ's
+transition or row failing does not cascade to the others), but
+multi-decision-per-writ shapes fail-loud-skip the entire tick.
+
